{{orphan|date=July 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Gunilla Gerland | image = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1963|07|13}} | birth_place = [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]] | nationality = [[Sweden|Swedish]] | known_for = writer on [[Asperger Syndrome]] | website = [http://www.pavus.se/ www.pavus.se] }} '''Gunilla Gerland''' (born 1963, in [[Stockholm]]) is an author, lecturer and debater on the topic of [[Asperger syndrome]].
Her 1996 autobiography entitled ''A Real Person: Life on the Outside'' (original Swedish title: ''En riktig människa''), described her life growing up with Asperger syndrome in an unsympathetic environment.<ref>Deborah R. Barnbaum, Indiana University Press, 2008 [https://books.google.com/books?id=RGgvf7ScEkwC&pg=PA106&lpg=PA106&dq=%22Gunilla+Gerland%22&source=bl&ots=wk2PGSPx7z&sig=lJv0JVySswq1lRxTrFTKJygAYlw&hl=en&sa=X&ei=paDqU4fnOdHfsATxg4KgAw&ved=0CIEBEOgBMA44Cg#v=onepage&q=%22Gunilla%20Gerland%22&f=false The Ethics of Autism: Among Them, But Not of Them], (see "Voices of Autism" section) Retrieved August 12, 2014</ref><ref>Suzanne Zeedyk (editor), 2008, Jessica Kingsley Publishers, [https://books.google.com/books?id=j8FlobYFiW0C&pg=PA180&lpg=PA180&dq=%22Gunilla+Gerland%22&source=bl&ots=alAGN_p59J&sig=70fD8_oqI3d2ssI0AToKbYAu95k&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JaLqU7LjC9XKsQS2n4LwBg&ved=0CG0Q6AEwCDhu#v=onepage&q=%22Gunilla%20Gerland%22&f=false Promoting Social Interaction for Individuals with Communicative Impairments ...], (see page 180), Retrieved August 12, 2014</ref><ref>Allen Shawn, 2011, Viking Publishers, [https://books.google.com/books?id=l8-UDU56wQgC&pg=PT24&lpg=PT24&dq=%22Gunilla+Gerland%22&source=bl&ots=0mF8ZYNUU7&sig=FzSNnVJ-b2QI_lrDv4j6DOJ6fJQ&hl=en&sa=X&ei=JaLqU7LjC9XKsQS2n4LwBg&ved=0CG8Q6AEwCThu#v=onepage&q=%22Gunilla%20Gerland%22&f=false Twin: A Memoir], (see last page of Chapter 2), Retrieved August 12, 2014</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Gerland |first=Gunilla |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/the-human-condition-my-family-and-other-strangers-1235421.html |title=The Human Condition: My family and other strangers |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |date=12 October 1997 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/162806.article |last=Tucker |first=Nicholas |title=Prisoner in an inner world |newspaper=[[The Times|Times Higher Education Supplement]] |date=18 May 1998 }}</ref>
She has continued to write<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.tes.co.uk/article.aspx?storycode=336949 |title=Publications |newspaper=TES |date=14 July 2000}}</ref> and also to lecture<ref name=xoomer>{{cite web |last=Gerland |first=Gunilla |title=Living with an autistic disability |url=http://xoomer.virgilio.it/marpavio/Gunilla_Gerland_Living_with_an_autistic_disability.htm |publisher=xoomer.virgilio.it |date=1999 |accessdate=16 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |first=Ol'ga |last=Bogdashina |title=Sensory Perceptual Issues in Autism and Asperger Syndrome: Different Sensory Experiences, Different Perceptual Worlds |location=London/New York |publisher=Jessica Kingsley |year=2003 |isbn=9780585471112 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RCQ1U38WmjIC&pg=PA14&lpg=PA14&dq=Gerland,+%22A+Real+Person%22&source=bl&ots=uYO3QS3wQy&sig=s_OXbtPZQPem9f20dJEpmmzsSfY&hl=en&sa=X&ei=H7XqU_XDKYbvoASKoYLAAw&ved=0CBwQ6AEwADgU#v=onepage&q=Gerland%2C%20%22A%20Real%20Person%22&f=false |page=14 |quotation=For our audience her conference on sensory problems really was an eye-opener. }}</ref> and debate on Asperger syndrome and on the [[autism spectrum]]. She works as a counsellor and educator in the field in Stockholm.<ref name=jkp>{{cite web |title=Gunilla Gerland |url=http://www.jkp.com/catalogue/author/366 |publisher=Jessica Kingsley Publishers |accessdate=12 August 2014 }}</ref> Her writings have been cited in work concerning the autism spectrum<ref>{{cite book |first=Maria |last=Rhode |chapter=What Does It Feel Like? Two First-Person Accounts by Adults with Asperger's Syndrome |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Q6C46AptiLEC&pg=PA70 |title=The Many Faces of Asperger's Syndrome |editor1-first=Maria |editor1-last=Rhode |editor2-first=Trudy |editor2-last=Klauber |location=London/New York |publisher=Karnac |year=2004 |series=Tavistock Clinic series |isbn=9781849404495 |pages=70&ndash;85}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KcsS2OGq8wsC&pg=PA279&lpg=PA279&dq=Gerland,+%22En+riktig+m%C3%A4nniska%22&source=bl&ots=AKdJA46kI1&sig=PykNfQW-7bD_CExidq_D1rw_pvk&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qJrqU_yzIcWBiwLSq4HoBA&ved=0CEYQ6AEwBTgU#v=onepage&q=Gerland&f=false |first=Sonia |last=Sharp |chapter=Preventing and managing specific learning difficulties in the classroom |title=A Neurodevelopmental Approach to Specific Learning Disorders |editor1-first=Kingsley |editor1-last=Whitmore |editor2-first=Hilary |editor2-last=Hart |editor3-first=Guy |editor3-last=Willems |series=Clinics in developmental medicine |volume=145 |location=London |publisher=Mac Keith |year=1999 |isbn=9781898683117 |pages=259–279}}</ref> and autism-related problems such as [[prosopagnosia]],<ref>{{cite journal |url=http://ww2.lakartidningen.se/old/content_0441/pdf/3191.pdf |last=Hagström |first=Torbjörg |title=Att inte känna igen ansikten – ingen bagatell för den drabbade |journal=Läkartidningen |volume=101 |issue=41 |year=2004 |page=3191 |language=Swedish }}</ref> in addition to ways in which autism is analysed and discussed.<ref>{{cite book |last=Stubblefield |first=Anna |chapter=Knowing Other Minds: Ethics and Autism |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bb0cAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA158&lpg=PA158&dq=Gerland,+%22A+Real+Person%22&source=bl&ots=GP-Dm24s-Q&sig=9EbL2BS7VPl0G4xCt09eQSOV9SE&hl=en&sa=X&ei=DqXqU9GFJoPvoASwt4CABw&ved=0CFAQ6AEwDDgK#v=onepage&q=Gerland%2C%20%22A%20Real%20Person%22&f=false |title=The Philosophy of Autism |editor1-first=Jami L. |editor1-last=Anderson |editor2-first=Simon |editor2-last=Cushing |location=Lanham, Maryland |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |year=2013 |isbn=9781442217072 |pages=158, 159 }}</ref>
