{{Other people|Peter Marshall}} {{more citations needed|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Peter Marshall | honorific_prefix = | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1939 | birth_place = | death_date = 1972 | death_place = [[Surrey]], [[England]] | resting_place = | occupation = Novelist | language = | nationality = {{flagicon|UK|}} British | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = <!-- or: | notablework = --> | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = [[John Llewellyn Rhys Prize]] | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = 1962-1966 | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }} '''Peter Marshall''' (1939-1972) was a [[British people|British]] [[novelist]].
== Life == Peter Marshall was born in 1939.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5311527.Peter_Marshall|title=Peter Marshall|accessdate=25 June 2015|publisher=[[Goodreads]]}}</ref> At 18 years old he became infected with [[Poliomyelitis|polio]], which left him almost completely paralyzed. He wrote an autobiography (''Two Lives'') about his life before and after the illness, for which he received the [[John Llewellyn Rhys Prize]] in 1963.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foyles.co.uk/Public/Biblio/PrizeDetails.aspx?prizeId=1019|title=The John Llewellyn Rhys Prize|accessdate=25 June 2015|publisher=[[Foyles]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.literaryfestivals.co.uk/book_award_results/llwellynrhys.html|title=The John Llewellyn Rhys Prize|accessdate=25 June 2015|website=Literaryfestivals.co.uk}}</ref> He wrote two novels, ''The Raging Moon'' (1964) and ''Excluded from the Cemetery'' (1966). The movie ''[[The Raging Moon]]'' was based on his novel by the same title. He lived and worked in a home in [[Surrey]]. He died at age 33 in 1972.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0551104|title=Peter Marshall|accessdate=25 June 2015|publisher=[[IMDb]]}}</ref>
