'''Sam J. Reid''' (born 7 November 1989) is a professional [[Australian rules football]]er playing for the [[Greater Western Sydney Giants]] in the [[Australian Football League]] (AFL). He previously played for the {{AFL WB}}.

Reid was drafted to the [[Western Bulldogs]] with the 35th selection in the [[2007 AFL draft]]. The young [[Queensland]]er is a medium-sized midfielder, and debuted against [[Adelaide Football Club|Adelaide]] in the final round of the regular season of [[2008 AFL season|2008]].

In 2009, he had major groin surgery for his osteitis pubis. This surgery was thought to have also triggered his Type 1 diabetes which shortly followed the surgery.<ref>http://www.theage.com.au/afl/afl-news/bulldog-has-diabetes-but-is-ok-to-play-on-20100123-mrrx.html</ref>

In 2011 he was recruited by the new Greater Western Sydney Giants as an uncontracted player.<ref>[http://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/afl/more-action-to-come-on-day-four/story-fn69a32t-1226165490224 Trade week updates - day four]</ref>  He made his debut for the Giants in their Round 5 match against the Bulldogs in Canberra at [[Manuka Oval]].<ref>[http://news.smh.com.au/breaking-news-sport/sheedy-makes-hit-list-of-gws-critics-20120427-1xq0g.html Sheedy makes hit list of GWS critics]</ref>

After being delisted at the end of the 2013 season, Sam accepted a role from the Giants to stay at the club in a coaching role (development coach).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gwsgiants.com.au/video/2013-11-06/reid-steps-into-coaching|title=Reid Steps Into Coaching|date=6 November 2013|work=GWSGiants.com.au|publisher=[[Bigpond]]|accessdate=28 November 2015}}</ref>

He was re-drafted by Greater Western Sydney in the [[2015 AFL draft|2016 rookie draft]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gwsgiants.com.au/news/2015-11-27/second-chance-saloon|title=Second Chance Saloon|date=27 November 2015|work=GWSGiants.com.au|publisher=[[Bigpond]]|accessdate=28 November 2015}}</ref> He was delisted again at the conclusion of the 2017 season, however, the club has stated they may re-draft him in the [[2017 AFL draft|2018 rookie draft]] if he still available.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.afl.com.au/news/2017-10-31/giants-cut-veteran-forward-reid-ahead-of-deadline|title=Giants cut veteran forward for the second time|last=Thompson|first=Matt|date=31 October 2017|work=AFL.com.au|publisher=Bigpond|accessdate=31 October 2017}}</ref>

