'''Shabtai Teveth''' ({{lang-he|שבתי טבת}}; 1925 – 1 November 2014), was an [[Israelis|Israeli]] historian and an anti-[[Revisionist Zionism|Revisionist]] author.
Teveth was born in 1925 and grew up in the worker' quarters at the Migdal Tzedek quarry, where his father worked, near [[Petah Tikvah]].<ref>[http://www.haaretz.com/news/israel/1.624423 Remembering Shabtai Teveth, David Ben-Gurion's official biographer], ''Haaretz''</ref> He began working as a journalist for the newspaper ''[[Haaretz]]'' in 1950, eventually becoming its political correspondent. In 1981, he was appointed Senior Research Fellow at the [[Moshe Dayan Center for Middle Eastern and African Studies]] at [[Tel Aviv University]].
Following the publication of his research into the murder of [[Haim Arlosoroff]], 1982, [[Menachim Begin]] - first Israeli Prime Minister elected from the Revisionist movement - ordered a Judicial Commission of Enquiry which concluded that Teveth was wrong to suggest the murder might have been carried out by two [[Revisionist Zionism|Revisionists]].
In his biography of [[David Ben-Gurion]], Teveth argues that Ben-Gurion did not instigate a policy of [[population transfer]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Segev |first=Tom |title=One Palestine Complete: Jews and Arabs under the British Mandate |publisher= Little, Brown and Company |year=2000 |isbn= 9780805065879 |page=407}}</ref>
In 2005, Teveth was awarded the [[Israel Prize]] for "lifetime achievement and special contribution to society and the State."
==Published works== *{{cite book|title=The tanks of Tammuz|year=1968|publisher=Schoken|location=Tel Aviv}} (English: {{cite book|title=The tanks of Tammuz|year=1969|publisher=Viking Press}}) An account of Israel's Armoured Corps during the 1967 war. *{{cite book|title=The cursed blessing: the story of Israel's occupation of the West Bank|year=1969|publisher=Weidenfeld & Nicolson|isbn=0-297-00150-7}} - Translated from Hebrew to English by Myra Bank (1970). *{{cite book|title=Moshe Dayan: the soldier, the man, the legend|year=1971|publisher=Schoken}} (English: {{cite book|title=Moshe Dayan: the soldier, the man, the legend|year=1973|publisher=Houghton Mifflin|ISBN=0-7043-1080-5}}) *{{cite book|title=Kin'at David (David's Jealousy)|year=1980|publisher=Schoken}} Two volumes. *{{cite book|script-title=he:רצח ארלוזורוב|trans-title=The Arlosoroff Murder|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=toMNAAAAIAAJ|accessdate=26 June 2011|year=1982|publisher=Schoken|language=Hebrew}} *{{cite book|title=Ben-Gurion and the Palestinian Arabs: from peace to war|year=1985|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-503562-9}} *''The Incarnations of Transfer in Zionist Thinking'' 1988. (Hebrew), Ha'aretz. * Charging Israel With Original Sin (www.commentarymagazine.com/article/charging-israel-with-original-sin/) *{{cite book|title=The evolution of "transfer" in Zionist thinking|year=1989|publisher=Moshe Dayan Center for Middle Eastern and African Studies, Shiloah Institute, Tel Aviv University}} *{{cite book|title=Ben-Gurion and the Holocaust|year=1996|publisher=Harcourt Brace & Co}} *{{cite book|title=The Burning Ground |year=1997 |publisher=Schoken |location=Tel Aviv}} Two Volumes. Biography of David Ben-Gurion. *{{cite book|title=Ben-Gurion's spy: the story of the political scandal that shaped modern Israel|year=1996|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=978-0-231-10464-7}}
